      <scopecontent id="aspace_a0296083cb08288d3cb85aab4abe8cdb">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <list listtype="unordered">
            <item>
               <ref actuate="onrequest" show="replace" target="ref12">I. Lecture Notes, 1915-1917, n.d.</ref>
            </item>
            <item>
               <ref actuate="onrequest" show="replace" target="ref53">II. Term Papers, 1915-1917, n.d.</ref>
            </item>
            <item>
               <ref actuate="onrequest" show="replace" target="ref69">III. Reviews and Notes, 1915-1917, n.d.</ref>
            </item>
         </list>
         <p>Riemer's notes and writings provide information about the curriculum and teaching methods at the Yale Divinity School during the period that he was a student there, 1915-1917. These notes supplement the papers of various faculty members held by the Yale Divinity Library, including those of Benjamin Wisner Bacon, Harlan Page Beach, Charles Reynolds Brown, Douglas Clyde Macintosh, Frank Chamberlin Porter, Henry Hallam Tweedy, and Williston Walker.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
